<worksheet label="ws-act-7-3-2">
  <page>
    <activity xml:id="act-7-3-2" workspace="3cm">
      <introduction>
        <p>
      Consider the differential equation
      <m>\frac{dy}{dt} = 6y-y^2</m>.

      </p>
      </introduction>
      <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-7-3-2-task-0">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Sketch the slope field for this differential equation on the axes provided.
          </p>
          <image width="50%" source="images/7_3_slopefield" />
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <image width="50%" source="images/7_3_Act2_slope_field_soln" />
        </answer>
        <solution>
          <p>
            The slope field for this differential equation is shown in the following figure.
          </p>
          <image source="images/7_3_Act2_slope_field_soln" width="50%" />
        </solution>
      </task>
      <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-7-3-2-task-1">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Identify any equilibrium solutions and determine whether they are stable or unstable.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <hint/>
        <answer>
          <p><m>y = 0</m> or <m>y = 6</m>; <m>y = 0</m> is unstable, <m>y = 6</m> is stable.
          </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
          <p>
            If <m>y</m> is an equilibrium solution,
            then <m>y</m> is constant so <m>\frac{dy}{dt} = 0</m>.
            Solving <m>0 = 6y - y^2</m>, we see that either <m>y = 0</m> or <m>y = 6</m>,
            which is also consistent with what we see in the slope field.  In addition, <m>y = 0</m> is unstable because nearby solutions tend away from <m>y = 0</m>, while <m>y = 6</m> is stable since nearby solutions tend to <m>y = 6</m>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </task>
      <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-7-3-2-task-2">
        <statement>
          <p>
            What is the long-term behavior of the solution that satisfies the initial value <m>y(0) = 1</m>?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <hint/>
        <answer>
          <p>
            The solution will tend to <m>y = 6</m>.
          </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
          <p>
            The long-term behavior of the solution that satisfies the initial value
            <m>y(0) = 1</m> is that the solution will tend to <m>y = 6</m>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </task>
